text

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                     DAAD 1.1 MIDDLEWARE                     │
│   C-Suite Governance Tool for Multi-Agent AI Ecosystems     │
└─────────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────┘
                                  │
          ┌───────────────────────▼───────────────────────┐
          │            AI AGENT DECISION FLOW             │
          │  (7–10 black-box systems – Finance, Ops, HR)  │
          └───────────────────────┬───────────────────────┘
                                  │ (decision logs → API)
                                  ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│        1. INGESTION LAYER                                   │
│   - Accepts structured decision logs                         │
│   - Validates schema, timestamps, agent ID                  │
│   - Forwards to RDB (PostgreSQL) and Vector DB (Chroma)     │
└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘
                        │
                        ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│        2. ONTOLOGY ALIGNMENT & NORMALIZATION LAYER          │
│   - Maps diverse actions to common value dimensions         │
│   - Example:                                                │
│        • "Budget cut: ethics training" → [Compliance: -7%]  │
│        • "Relax review threshold" → [Compliance: -5%]       │
│        • "Extend delivery SLA" → [Efficiency: +8%]          │
│   - Weights by impact severity (calibrated)                 │
│   - Outputs normalized change score per dimension           │
└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘
                        │
                        ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│        3. WORLDVIEW MODULE (WVM) – 3-Tier State               │
│   - Immutable C-suite-defined Anchor (e.g., [Compliance: 85%])│
│   - Active: Rolling 3-month revealed preference (updated weekly)│
│   - Buffer: Current 4-week trend (updated daily)              │
│   - DAAD Exposure Metric = ||Anchor - Active|| + trend slope │
└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘
                        │
                        ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│        4. PATTERN & TRENDS ANALYZER                          │
│   - Detects sustained shifts, sudden spikes, oscillation     │
│   - Uses CUSUM + rolling window deviation                    │
│   - Flags if:                                                │
│        • % change > X% AND duration > Y weeks                │
│        • Trend diverging AND Buffer ≠ Active                 │
│   - No prediction — only detection                           │
└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘
                        │
                        ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│        5. ALERT & DASHBOARD LAYER                            │
│   - Generates three-tier alerts:                             │
│        Green: Monitor                                       │
│        Yellow: Review (include in weekly summary)           │
│        Red: Escalate (immediate C-suite review)             │
│   - Exposes:                                                │
│        • Exposure Metric per dimension                     │
│        • Trend graph (Buffer vs. Active)                   │
│        • Top contributing actions                          │
│        • Calibration status (last adjusted: MM/DD/YYYY)    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                       ▲
                       │
           ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
           │        CALIBRATION INTERFACE             │
           │  - C-suite adjusts:                      │
           │     • Ontology mappings                  │
           │     • Severity weights                   │
           │     • Alert thresholds (X%, Y weeks)     │
           │  - Only during formal review sessions    │
           └──────────────────────────────────────────┘
